caption.text:
Day 8: The Iron Lords 🔔
Even though The Taken King is my favorite expansion, I have to give credit to Rise Of Iron. Truly and amazing dlc and had an amazing soundtrack above all.
The last three videos include the songs in this order of the videos: Elegy, Lords Lost, Rise of Iron.
I think the Wrath of the Machine raid was fun, and I enjoyed the puzzle to getting outbreak ❤
Truly reskining the fallen to Siva was also something amazing to see. Gorgeous textures, and the change of earth as well as a new social space was epic!
Enjoy my edits I made!

This is my entry for @gcustomscreations contest. This is the finale stand. One of the planets humanity has lost during the war. There for the name of this is "loosing hope". But how i got into this hobby was back when mega first game out one of my friends brought his over to show me. So i saved enough up bought like the first 4 sets that started buying them more an more. But some of yall who followed me for the first year knows i started with building legos and posting pics of mega here an there. But i met a few people who are in the community @mega_bliks @helljumper_warzone
@maverickrecon17
And few others who i got some inspiration to paint customs from. If it wasnt for yall who helped me get into painting figs i dont think i would of kept this account. 
And good luck to everyone who enters @gcustomscreations

Ner'zhul is originally the supreme shaman of the orcs of Draenor.  Once upon a time, when the orcs had never heard of the world of humans, the commander of the Burning Legion, Kil'jaeden, appeared to Ner'zhul.  The demon saw that the shaman was very capable of magic and endowed Ner'zhul with the power to command streams of magical energy, in return for devotion to the Legion.  Ner'zhul aided the demons in the fight against the draenei living in Draenor, but soon the shaman began to realize that the orcs were only pawns in the great game of the demons of the Legion.  Kil'jaeden, realizing that Ner'zhul no longer wants to help the Legion, but has his own plans, chose a new representative of the orc race - a student of Ner'zhul, Gul'dan.  Gul'dan received even greater demonic power and authority.  Fearing for his life, Ner'zhul went into the shadows and his name was no longer mentioned in the First or Second Wars with the Alliance.

If you look up the Muttley Alarm Clock on eBay only 1 Japanese one comes up. Its selling for over £70 so I really did get an amazing find today! I only paid £8 for it in Pandora's Box Emporium and I actually got the game for free in Sue Ryder because their card machine wasn't working and I had no change on me. The woman at the till said because I visit often, I could have it for free. :D
